rComments: Dr. Downie never has a frownie, and he plants knowledge in students heads like a gardener, but he's really a professor.  Pay attention on learning different types of organisms, like grass, if you want a pass.

I really enjoyed the selected readings from modern Kiswahili authors and the poetry was awesome (Kitandawili Natowa and Pakacha Pakachuka are favorites)!  I learned so much about Kiswahili cultural issues.  Take this class!

I took this class last semester and loved it!  Prof. Downie seems to really enjoy teaching and knows a lot about plant taxonomy.  If I could, I would take the class again (and try to improve my grade).
I took IB335 last term and loved it!  Didn't think I would, but it turned out great.  Prof. Downie ROCKS!

king of plants. He sometimes seems to have a telepathic connection with them. All of them in his office are green and flowery, not dead like the ones in my apartment. He knows so much about how to make them grow good, like using water instead of powerade to water them. An absolute genius, and who woulda guessed his favorite plant is a tree?!?!!
